Kohi (coffee in japanese) is a library that provides some similar functions
to the library of Borland, conio.

How to use:

Create/install library.

   sudo make install

Build your binary application.
 
   gcc -o my_app main.c -I/usr/local/include/ -L/usr/local/lib/ -lkohi

Uninstall library:

   sudo make uninstall


* main.c is to test the library.
